					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm sure I've already seem (maybe not for the NES though) carts using more than one ROM chip to simulate a larger chip. I was just wondering how could I go about doing that to a devcart.
<br />
<br />I'm sure it would have something to do with the highest address line  (from the mapper chip) and the /OE pins in the ROMs. You know, the highest address line will define which ROM to use, but how? Would I need any extra hardware for doing something like this?
<br />
<br />On a somewhat related issue, I was reading about Sega Genesis/Megadrive devcarts, and it seems that you can use 2 8-bit ROMs to simulate a 16-bit ROM that the console expects. Can anyone confirm that all you have to do for this to work is connect all the address lines to both ROMs, and combine D0-D7 from each ROM to form a 16-bit (D0-D15) value?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
